<div class="govuk-width-container">
  <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">
    How to create proposed sections
  </h1>
  <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">
    Example section
  </h2>
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <%= image_pack_tag("public/sections/proposed.svg", alt: "Proposed sections example") %>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <div class="govuk-body">
        <h2>Your sections must</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Be drawn to scale</strong> Usually 1:100 or 1:50 at A3 or A4
            size
          </li>
          <li><strong>Have a scale bar</strong></li>
          <li><strong>Have a unique drawing reference number</strong></li>
        </ul>
        <h2>You should include</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>An off-site datum point</strong> as a point of reference for levels
          </li>
          <li><strong>Floor to ceiling heights</strong> within the building</li>
          <li><strong>Eaves, foundations and retaining structures</strong> if they might encroach onto adjoining land</li>
          <li><strong>Voids</strong> if there are any within the building</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Your application may not be marked as valid if the drawings do not clearly
          and accurately describe the site and the proposed changes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <%= link_to "Back", public_planning_guides_path, class: "govuk-button" %>
  </div>
</div>
